abstract: Ikenna Ndugba scored 14 points with five assists as Bryant narrowly defeated Dartmouth 64-60 on Saturday.
snippet: Ikenna Ndugba scored 14 points with five assists as Bryant narrowly defeated Dartmouth 64-60 on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: HANOVER, N.H. — Ikenna Ndugba scored 14 points with five assists as Bryant narrowly defeated Dartmouth 64-60 on Saturday.
headline_main: Ndugba, Green Lead Bryant to 64-60 Win at Dartmouth
headline_print_headline: Ndugba, Green Lead Bryant to 64-60 Win at Dartmouth

abstract: Latinos in Arizona can show how it’s done.
snippet: Latinos in Arizona can show how it’s done.
lead_paragraph: PHOENIX — First there were seven. Then 50. Then thousands of people, mostly Latino and many undocumented, who held a vigil on the lawn outside of the Arizona State Capitol in the spring of 2010, praying that Gov. Jan Brewer would not sign an anti-immigrant bill, the most punitive in generations, which had sailed through the Republican-controlled Legislature.

abstract: The fire, the deadliest in the city’s history, broke out early on Saturday and quickly filled the building with smoke, inundating the upper floors, where several residents jumped from windows, an official said.
snippet: The fire, the deadliest in the city’s history, broke out early on Saturday and quickly filled the building with smoke, inundating the upper floors, where several residents jumped from windows, an official said.
lead_paragraph: Authorities said they were investigating whether a stove that was being used for heat ignited an early-morning fire in a Las Vegas apartment building on Saturday, killing six people and injuring 13 in the deadliest blaze in the city’s history.

abstract: Record rainfall and darkness has hit Seattle as a major storm begins to lift across western Washington on the first day of winter, though the region is still at risk for flooding, mudslides and avalanches.
snippet: Record rainfall and darkness has hit Seattle as a major storm begins to lift across western Washington on the first day of winter, though the region is still at risk for flooding, mudslides and avalanches.
lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Record rainfall and darkness has hit Seattle as a major storm begins to lift across western Washington on the first day of winter, though the region is still at risk for flooding, mudslides and avalanches.
headline_main: Record Rain, Darkness: Seattle Braces for Floods, Mudslides
headline_print_headline: Record Rain, Darkness: Seattle Braces for Floods, Mudslides

abstract: Greek police said Saturday they have arrested three people involved in the theft earlier this year of 4.2 million euros ($4.65 million) from the office of a security company in northern Greece.
snippet: Greek police said Saturday they have arrested three people involved in the theft earlier this year of 4.2 million euros ($4.65 million) from the office of a security company in northern Greece.
lead_paragraph: THESSALONIKI, Greece — Greek police said Saturday they have arrested three people involved in the theft earlier this year of 4.2 million euros ($4.65 million) from the office of a security company in northern Greece.
headline_main: Greek Police Arrest 3 for Theft From Security Company
headline_print_headline: Greek Police Arrest 3 for Theft From Security Company

abstract: The Communist Party is reviving traditional beliefs for political gain — while cracking down on some faiths.
snippet: The Communist Party is reviving traditional beliefs for political gain — while cracking down on some faiths.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — In the northern suburbs of this city is a small temple to a Chinese folk deity, Lord Guan, a famous warrior deified more than a millennium ago. Renovated five years ago at the government’s expense, the temple is used by a group of retirees who run pilgrimages to a holy mountain, schoolchildren who come to learn traditional culture and a Taoist priest who preaches to wealthy urbanites about the traditional values of ancient China.

abstract: The head of Argentina´s new cabinet under President Alberto Fernandez said on Saturday that the government would make a series of belt-tightening "public spending adjustments," just hours after the country´s senate gave final legislative approval to an emergency economic reform package touted by Fernandez as the country's best chance at sparking growth.
snippet: The head of Argentina´s new cabinet under President Alberto Fernandez said on Saturday that the government would make a series of belt-tightening "public spending adjustments," just hours after the country´s senate gave final legislative approval ...
lead_paragraph: BUENOS AIRES — The head of Argentina´s new cabinet under President Alberto Fernandez said on Saturday that the government would make a series of belt-tightening "public spending adjustments," just hours after the country´s senate gave final legislative approval to an emergency economic reform package touted by Fernandez as the country's best chance at sparking growth.
headline_main: Argentina´s Cabinet Chief Unveils Public Service Belt-Tightening Measures
headline_print_headline: Argentina´s Cabinet Chief Unveils Public Service Belt-Tightening Measures
